                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">While I'm not done yet, I appreciate the fact that eventually, someday, I will be.  I don't know when that day will be but there's no harm in planning for the future.  I enjoy massively multiplayer games.  I'd like to continue to have one to play with my friends. But which?
<br />

<br />
- I have no interest in WoW.  Please don't try to sell me on it or lambast me for this decision - I will ignore you and it will diminish the usefulness of this thread.
<br />

<br />
- I REALLY have no interest in EQ2.  I blame Sony's customer service for this.
<br />

<br />
- I play DAoC occasionally already, but I see Mythic as a friendly but bumbling company that doesn't really understand how people play their game anymore. Combine this with the Dark Age of Bot-A-Lot issue, and the game's slow wandering from what originally drew me in (A sense of cool mythology) and you have a game that I'll continue to dabble in, but can't see really inviting my friends to play with me.
<br />

<br />
-I play and love <a href="http://www.puzzlepirates.com" target="_blank" class="postlink">Puzzle Pirates</a> (Speaking of Innovation in MMORPGs... <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="icon_wink.gif" border="0" /> ) but it's not quite what I need in my MMORPG.  I'll keep playing it on the side though, and encourage everyone to try it.
<br />

<br />
- Saga of Ryzom looks interesting, though it loses a few points with me for the Reese's "You got your scifi in my fantasy!" effect, which is not usually something I go for. Still, it sounds like it has a cool world going for it.  I'm probably going to try the free trial and see.
<br />

<br />
- I am avoiding FFXI as a result of a general distaste for all things Final Fantasy.
<br />

<br />
- What I've heard of Lineage II doesn't sound like my kind of game, but I could be talked into trying it.
<br />

<br />
- I don't know much of anything about Guild Wars, Asheron's Call 2, or any of the other MMORPGs currently on the market.
<br />

<br />
So the question is...given the above info, what do you suggest?  Am I missing one of the major competitors (Sorry UO.)?   Should I just cling doggedly to EQ until the next round of stuff comes out?
<br />

<br />
Thoughts or opinions?</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
