It's not actually the fantasy genre I'm burned out on so much the "Gain Levels -> Get Loot -> Gain Levels -> Get Loot -> Gain Levels -> Get loot" grind that forms the focus of EQ/EQ2/WoW/DAoC.  Adding "Do some static 'quest'" to the grind doesn't really do anything for me when the game is still about becoming uber by gaining levels and getting loot.  Especially when those gains of levels and loot make you into some sort of superman compared to the lowly "level 1" plebes just entering the game.   That's the sort of advancement system that 7th grader's playing D&D would design, and I like to think I've grown out of it.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
